; Regression test for issue #1612: Adjustment accounts are not collapsed by -n (BZ#540)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1612
;
; When using `bal -n` (--collapse), synthetic <Adjustment> accounts created
; for display rounding compensation should be collapsed/suppressed.
; Without -n, these appear in bal output at the <Adjustment> top level.
; With -n, they should be collapsed (they have no parent to collapse into,
; so they are synthetic and should not appear).

2012-01-01 * Opening balance
    Assets:Current                         17.43 EUR
    Assets:Investments                200 "LU02" @ 24.77 EUR
    Assets:Investments                 58 "LU02" @ 24.79900855 EUR
    Equity:Opening balance

2012-01-27 * Test
    Income:Test                         -2759.50 GBP
    Income:Test                          -110.76 GBP
    Assets:Foo                            345.57 GBP
    Expenses:Test                          16.47 GBP
    Expenses:Test                           6.33 GBP
    Expenses:Test                         261.39 GBP
    Assets:Current

test bal -X EUR -H
         6415.57 EUR
         2586.07 GBP  Assets
           17.43 EUR
         2240.50 GBP    Current
          345.57 GBP    Foo
         6398.14 EUR    Investments
        -6409.77 EUR  Equity:Opening balance
          284.19 GBP  Expenses:Test
        -2870.26 GBP  Income:Test
--------------------
            5.80 EUR
end test

test bal -X EUR -H -n
         6415.57 EUR
         2586.07 GBP  Assets
        -6409.77 EUR  Equity
          284.19 GBP  Expenses
        -2870.26 GBP  Income
--------------------
            5.80 EUR
end test
